title: Bilal Ally, Hussein Howe, Devinn Waters headline Week 8 honor roll
text:
Bilal Ally, Hussein Howe, Devinn Waters headline Week 8 honor roll 
By The Times-Union Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 11:03 pm A glance at the area's top high school football performances from Week 8. Bilal Ally, RB, Clay: Had 340 rushing yards and another 129 on kickoff returns in the Blue Devils’ 56-35 win over Ridgeview. Ally had six rushing TDs and one on a kickoff return. Tyrus Cook, QB, Union County: Was 31 of 47 passing for 462 yards and four TDs in a 44-41 loss to Fort White. Palatka defense and RB Dontaeveone Evans: Evans rushed for 143 yards and three second-half TDs as the Panthers hammered Menendez, 30-0. Palatka’s defense allowed just 191 total yards and forced a pair of turnovers Hussein Howe, RB-LB, University Christian: Had 260 yards on 16 touches and four total TDs in a 61-18 rout of Cedar Creek Christian. Michael McCray, WR, Ribault: Had six catches for 157 yards and a pair of TDs in a 29-18 loss to Suwannee. JD Pirris, WR, Nick Tronti, QB, Ponte Vedra: Tronti was 10 of 17 passing for 365 yards and four TDs as the Sharks routed Kenny 36-7. Pirris had 179 yards and a TD on five catches. Donald Robinson, RB, Demetric Jackson, QB, Fort White: Robinson had 167 yards and three TDs on 11 touches in a 44-41 comeback win over Union County. Jackson was 13 of 21 passing for 187 yards and a TD, and rushed for 70 yards and a pair of TDs and a two-point conversion. Devinn Waters, DB, Mandarin: Intercepted two passes and returned one 35 yards for a TD in a 52-29 win over Sandalwood. Also returned a punt 32 yards for a score.
